---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Recovery — DID One" description="Recover or retire as a platform law.">
  <main class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="badge">Recover or Retire</div>
      <h1>Recovery path for everything</h1>
      <p class="lede">A stable system is not one that never fails. A stable system is one where every failure already has a governed path home.</p>
      <div class="panel">
        <pre class="code-card">Failure does not mean death.
Concern does not mean freeze.
Residue does not surface as truth.
Repair must be possible.
Exit must be graceful.
History must remain verifiable.</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="card"><h3>Recover</h3><p>Constrain, repair, verify, re-certify, and restore when trust can be rebuilt.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Retire</h3><p>Gracefully exit, hand off, archive, and preserve verification when recovery fails.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Compatibility</h3><p>Old DID documents, credentials, receipts, and proofs must remain readable and verifiable.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
